  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Fundamental Principles and Rights at Work In Sri Lanka</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Advocacy for international labour standards, labour law, fundamental principles and rights at work (child labour, forced labour, non-discrimination in the workplace, freedom of association and collective bargaining); formalisation of informal work, occupational safety and health.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This award supports advocacy for international labor standards, labor law, fundamental principles and rights at work. More specifically, this includes Bringing the legal framework into conformance with ILS. Strengthening LMR and effective labor administration.</narrative>
  </description>
